unittitle_ssm: Victorian Society in America, Metropolitan Chapter records
abstract_ssm: Since 1966, the Victorian Society in America (VSA) has been committed to protecting, promoting, and preserving Victorian-era (1837-1901) and Edwardian-era (1901-circa 1914) arts, architecture, and culture in the United States. The collection includes print and digital administrative records, correspondence, publications, and ephemera of the founding and early years of the Victorian Society in America (circa 1966-1970) and of the Metropolitan Chapter of the VSA (1970-2018).
